<dl id="n15029f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15029f">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15029f"> 29(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">+</font> to Iceland / 1000 yrs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In <mark>the year 1000</mark>, after a stubborn but short resistance on the part of those who favoured the old faith, <mark>Christianity was formally adopted by law as the religion of Iceland</mark>. This in time naturally brought with it the culture of the mediaeval church, and a knowledge of Latin. <small> W. A. Craige, <a name="ICEL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ICEL"><cite title="source">The Icelandic Sagas</cite></a>, (1913) 19-20</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15205f" href="c15all.htm#c15205f">VI.C.15:205(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
